{# Page navigation: attr_sheet_tab is set by the sheet worker on button click
   (see src/workers/inventory.js), not by a radio's :checked state. Roll20
   discourages label[for]/input[id] pairing (multiple copies of the same
   sheet can be in the DOM at once, one per open character, so ids collide)
   — a plain radio/label pair is unreliable there. Buttons + worker is the
   same mechanism already used for every other interactive element on the
   sheet (grimoire, trash, purse, bag nav), so it's proven to work.
   CSS in src/css/tabs.css shows the page + ribbon set matching
   attr_sheet_tab's value directly; the .sheet-book background swap lives
   there too. To add a page: add a button here, a partial in partials/pages/,
   its CSS in src/css/pages/, and the matching rules in tabs.css. #}
<input type="hidden" class="sheet-hand-mirror" name="attr_sheet_tab" value="base" />
<button type="action" class="sheet-nav-btn sheet-nav--magic" name="act_goto_magic"></button>
<button type="action" class="sheet-nav-btn sheet-nav--base" name="act_goto_base"></button>
<div class="sheet-nav-btn sheet-nav--map"></div>
<div class="sheet-nav-btn sheet-nav--questions"></div>
